@startuml "Orchestrators and Workflow Coordination"
title "Orchestrators: Specialized Workflow Handlers (SRP)"

' ==================== COMMAND ORCHESTRATOR ====================

package "Command Execution Orchestrator" {
  class CommandOrchestrator {
    + new(): Self
    --
    + handle_command(cmd, args, original_input, state, ui): async Result<()>
    - handle_clear_command(): Result<()>
    - handle_reload_aliases_command(): async Result<()>
    - handle_reload_commands_command(): Result<()>
    - handle_command_not_found(cmd, state)
    - execute_and_display(): async Result<()>
    - execute_interactive_and_display(): async Result<()>
  }

  note right of CommandOrchestrator
    **Single Responsibility**
    Orchestrates command execution workflow

    **Responsibilities**
    1. Handle application builtins (clear, reload-*)
    2. Verify command existence
    3. Check if command requires interactive mode
    4. Execute command via CommandExecutor
    5. Format and display output

    **Integrated Systems**
    - CommandExecutor: Actual execution
    - PackageInstaller: Auto-install (M2/M3)
    - ShellBuiltinHandler: Shell verification
    - TerminalUI: Interactive suspend/resume
    - TerminalState: Output buffering
  end note
}

' ==================== NATURAL LANGUAGE ORCHESTRATOR ====================

package "Natural Language Orchestrator" {
  class NaturalLanguageOrchestrator {
    - llm_client: Arc<dyn LLMClientTrait>
    - renderer: ResponseRenderer
    --
    + new(client, renderer): Self
    --
    + handle_query(query, state, ui): async Result<()>
    - stream_response(): async Result<()>
    - format_output(response): String
  }

  note right of NaturalLanguageOrchestrator
    **Single Responsibility**
    Orchestrates natural language query workflow

    **Responsibilities**
    1. Accept NL query from classifier
    2. Send to LLM client
    3. Render response with formatting
    4. Display in terminal
    5. Handle streaming (M2/M3)

    **Integrated Systems**
    - LLMClientTrait: Query interface
    - ResponseRenderer: Markdown formatting
    - TerminalState: Output buffering
    - TerminalUI: Display management

    **LLM Clients**
    - MockLLMClient: Development/testing
    - HttpLLMClient: Production (M2)
    - Future: OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.
  end note
}

' ==================== TAB COMPLETION HANDLER ====================

package "Tab Completion Handler" {
  class TabCompletionHandler {
    + new(): Self
    --
    + handle_tab_completion(state): Result<()>
    - find_completions(prefix): Vec<String>
    - get_command_completions(prefix): Vec<String>
    - get_file_completions(prefix): Vec<String>
  }

  note right of TabCompletionHandler
    **Single Responsibility**
    Orchestrates tab completion workflow

    **Responsibilities**
    1. Extract current word being completed
    2. Find matching completions (commands/files)
    3. Insert completion at cursor
    4. Update UI state

    **Completion Types** (M1)
    - Command names (from CommandCache)
    - File paths (filesystem lookup)

    **Future Enhancements** (M2/M3)
    - Bash/zsh integration
    - Subcommand completion
    - Option completion
    - History-based completion
  end note
}

' ==================== EXECUTOR AND DEPENDENCIES ====================

package "Execution Support" {
  class CommandExecutor {
    + execute(cmd, args, original): async Result<CommandOutput>
    + command_exists(cmd): bool
    + requires_interactive(cmd): bool
    + requires_shell_execution(cmd): bool
    - execute_with_timeout(cmd, args): async Result<CommandOutput>
  }

  class CommandOutput {
    + stdout: String
    + stderr: String
    + exit_code: i32
    --
    + is_success(): bool
    + combined_output(): String
  }

  class PackageInstaller {
    - package_manager: Box<dyn PackageManager>
    --
    + new(): Self
    + detect_package_manager(): Result<()>
    + install_package(package): async Result<()>
  }

  interface PackageManager {
    + name(): &str
    + is_available(): bool
    + install(package): async Result<()>
    + priority(): u8
  }

  note right of CommandExecutor
    **Responsibilities**
    - Async command execution
    - Timeout handling (configurable)
    - Output capture (stdout/stderr)
    - Exit code tracking
    - Interactive command detection
    - Shell builtin delegation

    **Interactive Commands** (28 supported)
    - Editors: vim, nvim, nano, emacs, vi, ed
    - Pagers: less, more, man, info
    - Tools: top, htop, watch, mc, ranger
    - Privilege: sudo
    - Requires TUI suspension/resumption

    **Blocked Interactive** (31)
    - Remote: ssh, tmux, screen, telnet
    - REPLs: python, node, mysql, psql
    - Debuggers: gdb, lldb
    - Browsers: w3m, lynx
  end note

  note right of PackageInstaller
    **Strategy Pattern**
    Abstracts package manager detection

    **Supported** (7 total)
    - Linux: apt, yum, dnf, pacman
    - macOS: brew
    - Windows: choco, winget

    **Priority Order**
    - Detects available PM on system
    - Falls back if unavailable
    - Prompts user (M2/M3)
  end note
}

' ==================== WORKFLOW INTEGRATION ====================

package "Terminal Coordination" {
  class InfrawareTerminal {
    Note: Main event loop coordinating all orchestrators
  }

  note right of InfrawareTerminal
    **Event Loop Integration**

    1. Poll terminal events
    2. Update state (input/history)
    3. On Submit:
       - Classify input via InputClassifier
       - Route to appropriate orchestrator:
         * InputType::Command → CommandOrchestrator
         * InputType::NaturalLanguage → NLOrchestrator
         * InputType::CommandTypo → Auto-correct + execute
    4. Render updated state
    5. Repeat

    **Orchestrator Responsibilities**
    - CommandOrchestrator: shell interaction
    - NLOrchestrator: LLM interaction
    - TabCompletionHandler: completion logic
  end note
}

' Relationships
CommandOrchestrator --> CommandExecutor : uses
CommandOrchestrator --> PackageInstaller : uses for install
CommandOrchestrator --> CommandOutput : processes
CommandExecutor --> "ShellBuiltinHandler" : verifies
PackageInstaller --> PackageManager : selects
CommandExecutor --> "Arc<Tokio>" : async execution
NaturalLanguageOrchestrator --> "Arc<dyn LLMClientTrait>" : queries
NaturalLanguageOrchestrator --> ResponseRenderer : formats
TabCompletionHandler --> CommandExecutor : finds completions via
InfrawareTerminal --> CommandOrchestrator : routes commands to
InfrawareTerminal --> NaturalLanguageOrchestrator : routes NL to
InfrawareTerminal --> TabCompletionHandler : handles completion

@enduml
